// Design Routes
// File-system handlers for CRUD operations on design files. Designs are stored
// as .design.json files under {project}/.collab/sessions/{session}/designs/.
// All handler IDs are sanitized to prevent path traversal before any file access.

FUNCTION sanitizeDesignId(id) -> string | null
  Return null if the input is empty or not a string.
  Strip any character that is not alphanumeric, hyphen, underscore, dot, or space.
  Return null if the sanitized result differs from the input, or if the input
  contains "..", "/", or "\". Otherwise return the sanitized string.

---

FUNCTION listDesignsHandler(req, res) -> Response                          EXPORT
  Read project and session from query params.
  List all files in the designs directory; ignore if directory is missing.
  For each file ending in ".design.json", collect its id, name, and mtimeMs.
  Return { designs: [...] }.

---

FUNCTION createDesignHandler(req, res) -> Response                         EXPORT
  Read project and session from query params; parse name and content from body.
  Sanitize the name. Return 400 if invalid.
  Build the file path and create any missing parent directories.
  IF content is a string, write it directly; otherwise serialize it as JSON.
  Return { id, success: true }.

---

FUNCTION getDesignHandler(req, res) -> Response                            EXPORT
  Sanitize the id from query params. Return 400 if invalid.
  Build the file path from project, session, and id.
  Return 404 if the file does not exist.
  Read file content as a string and retrieve its mtimeMs.
  Return { id, content (as raw string), lastModified }.

---

FUNCTION updateDesignHandler(req, res) -> Response                         EXPORT
  Sanitize the id from query params. Return 400 if invalid.
  Build the file path from project, session, and id.
  Return 404 if the file does not exist.
  IF content is a string, write it directly; otherwise serialize as JSON.
  Return { success: true }.
